<DATE>03/12/2008</DATE>
<AUTHOR>Victor G Zilinskas</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>I have the Sport model. Exciting car to drive with all the extras that a driver could desire. I don't find the control center confusing, but rather find it loaded with useful features. I push the car hard on winding roads and I find it very responsive and easy to handle. (It compares favorable to BMWs I owned in the past.) The gas mileage is not good, but that is the only disappointment (especially when premium hit $4.00 in Santa Barbara.) All together, I highly reccomend this reasonable priced luxury sport sedan. </TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Handling/performance; Blue Tooth; all control/data features. Comfortable ride.</FAVORITE>
